  "interpretation": "Rufus computes FAT size from total sectors, two FATs and four-byte FAT32 entries; aligns the reserved-plus-FAT system area to 1 MiB; uses root cluster 2, FSInfo sector 1 and backup boot sector 6; and rejects fewer than 65536 clusters or a total sector count reaching 0xffffffff. The repository narrows the first FreeDOS checkpoint to 512-byte sectors, a 1 MiB MBR partition start and a 1 MiB tail reservation."
